        <num>CCP 2252</num>
        <heading>2252.  Delay before proceeding with execution</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 2252.  Delay before proceeding with execution
A judgment creditor may proceed with the execution of a judgment only after the delay for a suspensive appeal therefrom has elapsed; however, recordation of a judgment in the mortgage records prior to the lapsing of the delay for a suspensive appeal does not begin proceedings for the execution of the judgment.</p>
        </content>
